title: Fishing_Location_Dialogue_Stab
---
//Triggering dialogue is handled externally. Yarn nodes assume they begin immediately after the object click or event triggers it via Unity.
//start "Fishing_Location_Dialogue_Stab" after mousedown on the fishing area.
<<set $fishingarea = floor(random_range(1, 4))>>
<<if $fishingarea == 1>>
    You: That looks promising.
    <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<if $fishingarea == 2>>
    You: I think I saw something jump!
    <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<if $fishingarea == 3>>
    You: That's a classic fishing hole!
    <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<if $fishingarea == 4>>
    You: Fancy fish for dinner?
    <<stop>>
    <<endif>>
<<stop>>
===